  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Assistant Student Care Mentor",
  "description": "<p>Responsibilities: -<br />As an Assistant Student Care Mentor, you will be working closely with children (7 - 12 years old) and make a positive difference in their lives. Your key responsibilities include: <br /></p><ul><li>executing day to day operations in the centre</li><li>ensuring safety and well-being of the children at all times</li><li>assisting lead mentor(s) to provide guidance and supervision of children in their school and other academic assignments</li><li>coaching and testing children for their school spellings</li><li>assisting in the preparation and co-conducting in-house enrichment curriculum with quality</li><li>building a positive and respectful relationship with children</li><li>Managing and guiding children to develop positive habits and mannerisms</li><li>executing holiday activities or special events for the children during school holidays</li><li>other related duties as assigned by the Centre Supervisor or Manager</li></ul><p>Requirements: -<br /></p><ul><li>Passionate in reaching out and empowering school children</li><li>Ability to manage a group of 10 to 15 children using positive management strategies</li><li>Ability to coach or guide children in their academics assignments</li><li>Enjoys working in a high-energy and dynamic environment</li><li>Has good interpersonal skills and is a good team player</li><li>Independent, observant, organised, responsible and takes initiative</li><li>Open to learning new skills and be trained</li><li>Minimum GCE 'O' level</li><li>Can speak the Chinese language to teach Chinese</li><li>Some relevant working experience preferred</li><li>Working hours: 12.30 pm to 7 pm Mondays to Fridays</li></ul>",
